642
00:29:02,360 --> 00:29:05,600
Here are six ways that one can combat loneliness.

643
00:29:05,600 --> 00:29:07,680
Number one, reach out.

644
00:29:07,680 --> 00:29:09,600
This could include professional help

645
00:29:09,600 --> 00:29:12,120
or expressing how you feel to your friends or family.

646
00:29:12,120 --> 00:29:14,000
You can just start small.

647
00:29:14,000 --> 00:29:16,720
You could also find local groups, organizations,

648
00:29:16,720 --> 00:29:19,640
and services that can help you connect with others.

649
00:29:19,640 --> 00:29:21,520
Reach out to a mental health professional

650
00:29:21,520 --> 00:29:23,040
like a therapist or counselor.

651
00:29:23,040 --> 00:29:25,240
They can provide you with guidance and support

652
00:29:25,240 --> 00:29:27,840
to address the underlying causes of loneliness.

653
00:29:28,760 --> 00:29:31,180
Number two, self-acceptance.

654
00:29:31,180 --> 00:29:33,740
This seems counterintuitive, but another solution

655
00:29:33,740 --> 00:29:36,780
is to cultivate a connection with oneself.

656
00:29:36,780 --> 00:29:38,260
It's a practice to remind us

657
00:29:38,260 --> 00:29:40,540
that we do indeed have self-worth.

658
00:29:40,540 --> 00:29:43,700
A 2022 study showed that self-reflection

659
00:29:43,700 --> 00:29:45,420
can reduce feelings of loneliness

660
00:29:45,420 --> 00:29:48,860
and also contribute to finding meaning in life.

661
00:29:48,860 --> 00:29:52,060
Reflecting on who you are, practicing self-compassion,

662
00:29:52,060 --> 00:29:55,480
and writing down how you're feeling can be a great start.

663
00:29:55,480 --> 00:29:57,400
Number three, gratitude.

664
00:29:58,400 --> 00:30:01,640
A lot of things around us tell us that we're not enough.

665
00:30:01,640 --> 00:30:04,360
It's how a lot of companies make their money.

666
00:30:04,360 --> 00:30:06,840
The advertising tells us we're not rich enough

667
00:30:06,840 --> 00:30:07,800
or pretty enough.

668
00:30:07,800 --> 00:30:11,080
Although if we just buy this one more thing, we'll be happy.

669
00:30:11,080 --> 00:30:13,040
We can combat this by being grateful

670
00:30:13,040 --> 00:30:16,280
in what we do have, the practice of gratitude.

671
00:30:16,280 --> 00:30:17,680
I know it sounds trite,

672
00:30:17,680 --> 00:30:20,480
but the simple practice of gratitude can do wonders.

673
00:30:20,480 --> 00:30:23,580
A 2021 study showed that increased gratitude

674
00:30:23,580 --> 00:30:25,640
can reduce feelings of loneliness.

675
00:30:25,640 --> 00:30:29,880
A 2015 study, 2011 study, and 2010 study

676
00:30:29,880 --> 00:30:31,920
all showed the same thing.

677
00:30:31,920 --> 00:30:33,440
For just five minutes a day,

678
00:30:33,440 --> 00:30:35,800
really think about what you can be thankful for.

679
00:30:35,800 --> 00:30:37,800
At first, it may seem like there's nothing

680
00:30:37,800 --> 00:30:40,600
to be thankful for, but if you're not forced

681
00:30:40,600 --> 00:30:43,320
to fight in a war, have a roof over your head

682
00:30:43,320 --> 00:30:46,080
and are in decent physical health, have food,

683
00:30:46,080 --> 00:30:48,760
and have water, that's better than some people.

684
00:30:48,760 --> 00:30:51,320
We should be thankful for that and much more.

685
00:30:51,320 --> 00:30:53,020
There's nothing wrong with acknowledging

686
00:30:53,020 --> 00:30:57,460
that where you are right now is hard, really, really hard,

687
00:30:57,460 --> 00:30:59,620
but incorporating the practice of gratitude

688
00:30:59,620 --> 00:31:02,940
alongside other support can strongly aid in your journey.

689
00:31:03,900 --> 00:31:06,580
For example, studies prove that gratitude

690
00:31:06,580 --> 00:31:09,260
can increase happiness, reduce depression,

691
00:31:09,260 --> 00:31:10,960
and strengthen resiliency.

692
00:31:12,740 --> 00:31:16,100
Grateful people often experience reduced blood pressure,

693
00:31:16,100 --> 00:31:20,320
less chronic pain, increased energy, even longer lives.

694
00:31:21,240 --> 00:31:23,680
People who purposefully express more gratitude

695
00:31:23,680 --> 00:31:26,200
report higher self-esteem than those who don't,

696
00:31:26,200 --> 00:31:28,400
and they're more likely to help others.

697
00:31:28,400 --> 00:31:33,000
A pro-social behavior also linked to greater happiness.

698
00:31:33,000 --> 00:31:35,360
People who capture grateful thoughts before bed

699
00:31:35,360 --> 00:31:37,800
sleep better than those who don't.

700
00:31:37,800 --> 00:31:39,920
Why so many positive changes?

701
00:31:39,920 --> 00:31:42,720
Because gratitude actually rewires our brains,

702
00:31:42,720 --> 00:31:46,320
kickstarting the production of dopamine and serotonin.

703
00:31:46,320 --> 00:31:49,520
Like antidepressants, these feel-good neurotransmitters

704
00:31:49,560 --> 00:31:51,680
activate the bliss center of the brain,

705
00:31:51,680 --> 00:31:54,600
creating feelings of happiness and contentment.

706
00:31:54,600 --> 00:31:57,040
This appears to be self-perpetuating.

707
00:31:57,040 --> 00:31:59,520
Research suggests that with regular practice,

708
00:31:59,520 --> 00:32:02,560
you'll train your prefrontal cortex to better appreciate

709
00:32:02,560 --> 00:32:05,120
and retain positive experiences and thoughts,

710
00:32:05,120 --> 00:32:07,920
and to deflect the negative ones.

711
00:32:07,920 --> 00:32:10,320
Number four, social media reduction.

712
00:32:11,240 --> 00:32:13,200
When it comes to using social media,

713
00:32:13,200 --> 00:32:15,520
we need to use it in moderation.

714
00:32:15,520 --> 00:32:17,840
There's research that says that a small amount

715
00:32:17,840 --> 00:32:19,600
of social media is beneficial,

716
00:32:19,600 --> 00:32:21,800
but a large amount is detrimental.

717
00:32:21,800 --> 00:32:24,200
30 minutes of use a day is the advice

718
